profile_positions.description:
-  Project lead and lead geoscientist in an integrated petrophysical and geological study of a large gas field in the Dniepr-Donets Basin, on behalf of a local gas operator.
- Coordinated an integrated petrophysics and geo-modeling study, that serves as an input to developing the client’s own integrated static and dynamical model;
- Developed a project study and modeling plan, monitored study progress and provided steer for the petrophysical as well as geological studies; 
- Intervened in study and adjusted work program and priorities, where needed;
- Communicated / liaised with the Technical Team of the client and  chaired conference calls;
- Liaised with several different technical groups which contributed to this large, integrated project, and were located in different locations, using internet-based meeting solutions.
- This study delivered a review and clean-up of the large well log stock of this field, and integrated petrophysical as well as Petrel geological modeling. 
- This integrated work serves as an input to developing the client’s own integrated static and dynamical model;
